Sequence Information.Peptide Name: cc-CATH2 (C. coturnix cathelicidin; natural AMPs; birds, animals; UCLL1a)

Literature Information.Literature: Activity: Active against Gram+ S. aureus ATCC 2592 (MIC 0.3 uM), clinical strains (MIC 20.2 uM or >26.9 uM), S. epidermidis (MIC 2.5 uM), S. haemolyticus IS 2401 or DRa (MIC 2.5 uM), N. asteroids, E. faecalis IS981 (MIC 1.3 uM), E. faecium IS 1299 (MIC 2.5 uM), P. acnes (MIC 1.3 uM), Gram-  K. oxytoca (MIC 2.5 uM), A. sobria, A. baumannii IS 2178 or Drb (MIC 1.3 uM), A. baumannii IS 2373 (MIC 2.5 uM), S. maltophilia (MIC 0.6-1.3 uM),  P. aeruginosa ATCC 27853, IS 1411-3 (MIC 10.1 uM), E. coli ATCC 27853 IS 1334-5(MIC 1.3-5.1 uM), K. pneumoniae IS strains (MIC 1..3-5.1 uM), P. vulgaris (MIC 10.1 uM), P. mirabilis, S. typhi IS 1408 (MIC 5.1 uM), fungi C. albicans ATCC 2002 (MIC 1.3 uM), C. glabrata IS 0902 (MIC 10.1 uM), and slime mold (MIC 0.6 uM).Antimicrobial robustness:  salt-insensitive: The antimicrobial activity did not change much in the presence of 100 mM NaCl.
